description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity to join Hull University Teaching Hospitals Catering service has become available. The successful applicant will work between Hull Royal Infirmary and Castle Hill Hospital within the Retail areas. Predominantly completing cooking duties within the kitchen areas and on occasions completing front of house tasks in a customer facing role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants would need to meet the essential criteria set out within the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is 30 hours per week on a fixed term for 6 months with a possible extension for 3 further months. the shift pattern will vary to meet the service demands and will include weekend and public holidays. the departments operate from 06:30am through to 08:00pm 7 days a week, shifts will vary throughout these operating hours and on occasions you may be asked to work later should any special events be taking place - Shifts would be agreed a minimum of two weeks in advance, on occasions slight amendments would be agreed through discussion at short notice should the service require this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to your own transport is desirable as from time to time you may be requested to work at an alternative site at short notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kevin Sewell Retail Catering Manager Kevin.Sewell@hey.nhs.uk 01482 875875 ext 3488&lt;/p&gt;
